RM  16707709
RT  Xanthosine utilization in Salmonella enterica serovar Typhimurium is
RT  recovered by a single aspartate-to-glycine substitution in xanthosine
RT  phosphorylase.
RA  Hansen MR, Tranekjaer JÃ¸rgensen J, Dandanell G;
RL  J Bacteriol. 2006;188:4153-4157.
CC  The three components of this system are xanthosine phosphorylase
CC  (XapA), xanthosine permease (XapB), together in a two-gene operon, and
CC  a constituitively expressed LysR-family positive regulator XapR, whose
CC  gene is just downstream from the xapAB operon. An open reading frame
CC  about 50 codons in length, found between xapB and xapR in Escherichia
CC  coli, although not characterized, appears to be conserved in species
CC  with XapABR and to have homologs in other genomic contexts in more
CC  distantly related species. Analysis by PSI-BLAST showed this is a
CC  conserved domain (see TIGR03510), and we name this small protein XapX.
**  The small hypothetical, ~ 50 amino acids, turns out to be real protein,
**  needs new HMM, project 2766.
